0.user_question: A chef needs to cook 12 potatoes. He has already cooked 6. If each potato takes 6 minutes to cook, how long will it take him to cook the rest?

ost_step.1: Identify the number of potatoes the chef still needs to cook. Since he needs to cook 12 potatoes and he has already cooked 6, this means he still needs to cook 12 - 6 = 6 potatoes.
ost_step.2: Multiply the number of potatoes the chef needs to cook by the time it takes to cook one potato. Each potato takes 6 minutes to cook, so for 6 potatoes, it would take 6 * 6 = 36 minutes.
